### Q_AGA: CODEC ANALOG GAIN
#
#   Range from 0 to XX (*~168db*)
#   Default value usually equals *0db* gain.
#
# !             Don't increase too much,                 !
# !    otherwise sound might distort/start crackling     !
#
#   Analog gain will inevitably raise the noise floor,
#   and the audible non-linear distortion will hit a lot
#   earlier. In this regard there is no need to set the
#   absolute maximum value and oversaturate the signal.
#
#   Use numbers within range, example: *Q_AGA=17*
#
Q_AGA=

### Q_HDGA: HEADPHONE DIGITAL GAIN
#
#   Range from 0 (*-84db*) to 124 (*+40db*)
#   Default value usually is 84 (*0db*)
#
# !             Don't increase too much,                 !
# !    otherwise sound might distort/start crackling     !
#
#   Digital gain is linear and doesn't introduce that
#   much of a problem, as analog might. However that
#   doesn't digital gain is bulletproof - it still
#   might bring harmonic & quantization noise. Balacning
#   analog & digital gain is the key to flawless
#   performance.
#
#   Might not work on some recent platforms with absent
#   gain controls.
#
#   Use numbers within range, example: *Q_HDGA=74*
#
Q_HDGA=

### Q_SDGA: SPEAKER DIGITAL GAIN
#
#   Range from 0 (*-84db*) to 124 (*+40db*)
