### Q_MBDRC: MULTI-BAND DRC
#
#   Disable speaker multi-band dynamic range compression.
#   Multiband compression divides the audio spectrum into
#   multiple frequency bands to reattenuate the level of
#   the louder parts of the signal to control peaks.
#   MBDRC has its downsides. Uneven frequency response -
#   where some frequency bands may be over while others
#   are under-compressed, which leads to tonal balance
#   shift, clipping artifacts, loss of contrast between
#   loud and quiet parts, due to over-compression, phase
# 	shifting distortion when certain frequencies cancel
# 	each other out or sound unnatural.
#
# 	          Might not work on some devices.
# !            CAN RESULT IN BUGS/SOUND LOSS            !
#
#   Set *Q_MBDRC=true* to force disable MBDRC, or leave
#   untouched for default behavior
#
Q_MBDRC=

### Q_FBUF: HAL FRAME BUFFER
#
#   The frame buffer in Audio HAL determines how many
#   audio frames are processed in each period before the
#   buffer is handed off to the next stage. It is important
#   to provide a wider buffer, the heavier (higher bitrate)
#   the source audio is.
#
#   You can choose between:
#   Latency   > more cpu intensive
#             > jittery due to frequent buffer
#               processing
#             > risk of buffer underruns
#             > ideal for real-time audio like
#               live processing, voip, gaming
#
#   Frames    > more power efficient
#             > smooth with fewer-to-none
#               processing interrupts
#             > less prone to buffer underrun
#             > best for hi-res / high bitrate
#               music content playback
#
# !                        NOTE                             !
#   Qcom/OEMs/OS may override parameters based on selected
#   stream or any other custom/internal logic.
#
# 	Set *Q_FBUF=latency* for lower latency
# 	Set *Q_FBUF=frames* for smooth fbuffer
#   Leave untouched for default behavior
#
Q_FBUF=

### Q_DSPOD: HW DSP OFFLOAD
#
#   HW DSP is used to decode & de/compress audio data
#   instead of cpu for better power efficiency. Qcom
#   DSP supports popular formats like mp3, flac, ape,
#   alac, aac to be offloaded. OffloadTrack derive
#   from DirectThread - meaning it acts much in the
#   same way - no mixing/sampling involved.
#
#   If *U_APFF=force* float format conversion is forced
#   you're better to disable offload, to let system
#   decode audio into float, bypassing dsp.
#
#   Set *Q_DSPOD=enable* to force enable offload
#   Set *Q_DSPOD=disable* to force disable offload
#   Leave untouched for default behavior
#
Q_DSPOD=

