### Q_BIQHPF: BIQUADS / HIGH-PASS FILTER
#
#   High-pass filter (HPF) is shaping audio tonal
#   balance by cutting low-frequency content off
#   while preserving the rest of ranges. Filter
#   applies a roll-off below a defined cutoff
#   frequency, with a slope that determines how
#   gradually or aggressively the low-end is
#   attenuated. Overuse of HPF can make a content
#   sound thin and unnatural, stripping warmth
#   from vocals and instruments. Over-filtering
#   can also remove ambient low-end reflections
#   that contribute to depth and space, making
#   a track feel unnaturally sterile and flat.
#
#   Additionally, on qcom, can be used as biQuads
#   filter - a second-order digital filter that 
#   acts as an EQ/IRS, but on codec (hw) level.
#
# 	          Might not work on some devices.
# !            CAN RESULT IN BUGS/SOUND LOSS            !
#
#   Set *Q_BIQHPF=true* to disable hpf/enable biQuads,
#   or leave untouched for default behavior
#   To use biQuads, please follow this thread:
#   https://xdaforums.com/t/mod-audio-biquads-utilizing-qualcomms-audio-codec-for-headphone-compensation.3093000
#
Q_BIQHPF=

