#   crackling or distorted sound
#
#   *Ex: T_CBIT=S16_LE*
#
T_CBIT=

### T_CBTSMPL: AOC CODEC BLUETOOTH SAMPLING
#
#   Codec could take following sampling options:
#   *SR_44P1K SR_48K SR_88P2K SR_96K SR_176P4K*
#   *SR_192K*
#
# 	*Ex: T_CBTSMPL=SR_44P1K*
#
T_CBTSMPL=

### T_CBTBIT: AOC CODEC BLUETOOTH BITWIDTH
#
#   Codec could take following format options:
#   *S16_LE S24_LE S24_3LE S32_LE*
#
#   You DON'T want to force higher discretization
#   on low source file, as results may end up in
#   crackling or distorted sound
#
#   *Ex: T_CBTBIT=S16_LE*
#
T_CBTBIT=

### T_FBUF: HAL FRAME BUFFER
#
#   The frame buffer in Audio HAL determines how many
#   audio frames are processed in each period before the
#   buffer is handed off to the next stage. It is important
#   to provide a wider buffer, the heavier (higher bitrate)
#   the source audio is.
#
#   You can choose between:
#   Latency   > more cpu intensive
#             > jittery due to frequent buffer
#               processing
#             > risk of buffer underruns
#             > ideal for real-time audio like
#               live processing, voip, gaming
#
#   Frames    > more power efficient
#             > smooth with fewer-to-none
#               processing interrupts
#             > less prone to buffer underrun
#             > best for hi-res / high bitrate
#               music content playback
#
# !          NOT ALL PIXELS SUPPORT THIS                   !
#
# 	Set *T_FBUF=latency* for lower latency
# 	Set *T_FBUF=frames* for smooth fbuffer
#   Leave untouched for default behavior
#
T_FBUF=
